***************************************************************************
:mod:`repoze.who.plugins.ldap` -- LDAP Authentication for WSGI Applications
***************************************************************************

:mod:`repoze.who.plugins.ldap` is an LDAP plugin for the identification and
authentication framework for WSGI applications, repoze.who, which acts as WSGI
middleware.
 
See the ``docs`` subdirectory of this package (also available at least
provisionally at http://static.repoze.org/whodocs) for more
information.


Install
=======

To install this repoze.who plugin, you should run:
    easy_install repoze.who.plugins.ldap

If you have problems to install it, they are very likely to be caused by
python-ldap: You will have to install it manually in order to set the correct
path to the OpenLDAP libraries. For more information, visit:
http://python-ldap.sourceforge.net/doc/html/installing.html


Bug reports and feature requests
================================

This plugin uses Launchpad.net as the bug tracking system:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/repoze.who.plugins.ldap
